#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/rerender-lazy-state-init.md
M|rules|title: Use Lazy State Initialization
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: wasted computation on every render
M|rules|tags: react, hooks, useState, performance, initialization
M|rules|Pass a function to `useState` for expensive initial values. Without the function form, the initializer runs on every render even though the value is only used once.
M|rules|**Incorrect (runs on every render):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function FilteredList({ items }: { items: Item[] }) {
M|rules|// buildSearchIndex() runs on EVERY render, even after initialization
M|rules|const [searchIndex, setSearchIndex] = useState(buildSearchIndex(items))
M|rules|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|rules|// When query changes, buildSearchIndex runs again unnecessarily
M|rules|return <SearchResults index={searchIndex} query={query} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|function UserProfile() {
M|rules|// JSON.parse runs on every render
M|rules|const [settings, setSettings] = useState(
M|rules|JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('settings') || '{}')
M|rules|)
M|rules|return <SettingsForm settings={settings} onChange={setSettings} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (runs only once):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function FilteredList({ items }: { items: Item[] }) {
M|rules|// buildSearchIndex() runs ONLY on initial render
M|rules|const [searchIndex, setSearchIndex] = useState(() => buildSearchIndex(items))
M|rules|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|rules|return <SearchResults index={searchIndex} query={query} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|function UserProfile() {
M|rules|// JSON.parse runs only on initial render
M|rules|const [settings, setSettings] = useState(() => {
M|rules|const stored = localStorage.getItem('settings')
M|rules|return stored ? JSON.parse(stored) : {}
M|rules|})
M|rules|return <SettingsForm settings={settings} onChange={setSettings} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|Use lazy initialization when computing initial values from localStorage/sessionStorage, building data structures (indexes, maps), reading from the DOM, or performing heavy transformations.
M|rules|For simple primitives (`useState(0)`), direct references (`useState(props.value)`), or cheap literals (`useState({})`), the function form is unnecessary.